definitions.definition: A transcontinental country in the Caucasus region of Europe and Asia , on the coast of the Black Sea , often considered to belong politically to Europe . Official name: Georgia . Capital: Tbilisi .

main_definition: A transcontinental country in the Caucasus region of Europe and Asia , on the coast of the Black Sea , often considered to belong politically to Europe . Official name: Georgia . Capital: Tbilisi .

definitions.definition: A state in the Southern United States . Capital: Atlanta . It is named for George II of Great Britain (1683–1760).
Several smaller places in the United States .

subdefinitions.definition: A town in Franklin County , Vermont , named for George III of the United Kingdom (1738–1820).
An unincorporated community in Lawrence County , Indiana , named for the state.
An unincorporated community in Cherry County , Nebraska , named for George A. Frost, a local carpenter.
An unincorporated community in Monmouth County , New Jersey .

definitions.definition: A hamlet in Towednack parish, Cornwall , England .
A transitional serif typeface named after the state, designed by Matthew Carter in 1993.
